{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"66d95718-ab38-477c-8e8e-b1b2a9a15463","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's going on:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Tests lost history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **default test ID format** to fully qualified names. Azure DevOps sees these as entirely new tests. Fix by adding to your `.runsettings`:\n\n```xml\n<MSTest>\n  <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n</MSTest>\n```\n\nOr keep the new IDs and accept a one-time history reset.\n\n### 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a **class-level context** — it no longer has an associated test method, so `TestName` throws. This context is only meant for class-level setup.\n\nFix your code — remove the `TestName` access:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // context.TestName is no longer available here in v4\n    // Use this context only for class-level logging/setup\n}\n```\n\nIf you need per-test setup, move that logic to `[TestInitialize]` where `TestContext` still has the test name.\n\n### 3. Other v4 breaking changes to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **`[DataRow]` type coercion** | Implicit type conversions (e.g., `int` → `long`) are stricter; mismatches may fail at compile time or runtime |\n| **`Assert.AreEqual` for collections** | Behavior was tightened; use `CollectionAssert` explicitly |\n| **Parallel execution** | Now enabled by default at the **method** level; tests assuming serial execution may break |\n| **`[DeploymentItem]`** | Behavior changed; paths resolve differently |\n| **`TestContext.Properties`** | Some legacy properties were removed |\n| **Nullable annotations** | `TestContext` properties now have nullable annotations; may produce warnings |\n\nThe parallel-by-default change is the most likely to cause subtle, intermittent failures if your tests share state. Add this to `.runsettings` if needed:\n\n```xml\n<MSTest>\n  <Parallelize>\n    <Scope>None</Scope>\n  </Parallelize>\n</MSTest>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"63710656-834d-4518-a1a2-fe0eba515703","outputTokens":569,"requestId":"044E:2310B5:25B376E:2A77EBA:69E83718"},"id":"7b243437-fa81-40f7-8417-d6f69435614e","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:49:09.670Z","parentId":"65889531-d950-4e83-87ad-5c2272f87b65"}
